, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Thomas Belgrave was born in 1365, in Belgrave, Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Rogerus Belgrave (III), was 30 and his mother, Margaret Rich, was 27. He married Lady Elizabeth Shelton in 1395, in Belgrave, Leicestershire, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"1365–":"1365–Surnud","1365–Male":"1365–Surnud","1370–1420":"1370–1420","1397–Male":"1397–Surnud","1335–Male":"1335–Surnud","1338–Female":"1338–Surnud","1338":"1338","1335":"1335","1365":"1365","1420":"1420","1397":"1397","1395":"1395","1370":"1370","Belgrave, Leicestershire, England":"Belgrave, Leicestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1365–":"1365–Kuollut","1365–Male":"1365–Kuollut","1370–1420":"1370–1420","1397–Male":"1397–Kuollut","1335–Male":"1335–Kuollut","1338–Female":"1338–Kuollut","1338":"1338","1335":"1335","1365":"1365","1420":"1420","1397":"1397","1395":"1395","1370":"1370","Belgrave, Leicestershire, England":"Belgrave, Leicestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1365–":"1365–Décédé","1365–Male":"1365–Décédé","1370–1420":"1370–1420","1397–Male":"1397–Décédé","1335–Male":"1335–Décédé","1338–Female":"1338–Décédée","1338":"1338","1335":"1335","1365":"1365","1420":"1420","1397":"1397","1395":"1395","1370":"1370","Belgrave, Leicestershire, England":"Belgrave, Leicestershire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Thomas Belgrave est né en 1365, à Belgrave, Leicestershire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, son père, Rogerus Belgrave (III), avait 30 ans et sa mère, Margaret Rich, avait 27 ans. Il a épousé La